One man was killed and two others were wounded during a shooting in the Bronx on Saturday evening, cops said. The three men were shot at around 7:40 p.m. on Clay Avenue near the Cross Bronx Expressway, according to police. A 27-year-old man was shot in the chest and was pronounced dead at St. Barnabas Hospital, according to police. A 39-year-old man was shot in the right leg and a 34-year-old man was shot in the left leg. Both were transported to Lincoln hospital and are expected to recover. A suspect fled the scene in a dark-colored sedan in an unknown direction. No arrests were immediately made on Saturday night.